To create a custom pipe for filtering data in a table based on a search input, you can implement a filtering logic inside the pipe's `transform` method. The goal is to filter the data based on the search keyword provided. 

Here's an example of how you can implement this logic in the custom pipe:

1. Create a new pipe using the Angular CLI:

```bash
ng generate pipe searchfilter
```

2. Update the `transform` method in the generated `searchfilter.pipe.ts` file to filter the data based on the search keyword:

```typescript
// searchfilter.pipe.ts

import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from '@angular/core';

@Pipe({
  name: 'searchfilter'
})
export class SearchfilterPipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(items: any[], searchText: string): any[] {
    if (!items) {
      return [];
    }
    if (!searchText) {
      return items;
    }

    searchText = searchText.toLowerCase();

    return items.filter(item => {
      // Implement your custom filtering logic here
      // For example, check if any property of the item contains the search text
      return Object.values(item).some(val => 
        val.toString().toLowerCase().includes(searchText)
      );
    });
  }
}
```

In this example logic:
- The pipe takes an array of items (`items`) and a search keyword (`searchText`) as arguments.
- It checks if the `items` array and `searchText` are defined and then proceeds to filter the array based on the search keyword.
- The `transform` method filters the `items` array by checking if any property of the item (converted to lowercase) contains the search text.
- The `return` statement uses `Object.values(item)` to access all property values and check if any of them include the search text.

3. Use the custom pipe in your template to filter the data in the table based on the search input:

```html
<tr *ngFor="let order of ordersList | searchfilter: searchedKeyword; let i = index">
  <!-- Table row content here -->
</tr>
```

With this custom pipe, the data displayed in the table will be filtered based on the search input provided, helping to enhance the user experience by allowing them to search and filter the table data dynamically. Feel free to adjust the filtering logic in the `transform` method to suit the specific requirements of your application.

